  "prompt": "Why do I need to incorporate my \"business\" to drive for Uber in Manila?",
  "response": "I apologize, but there's a misunderstanding. In Manila, you do not need to incorporate a business to drive for Uber (or more accurately, Grab, which replaced Uber in the Philippines in 2018). You typically just need to:\n\n1. Have a valid driver's license\n2. Meet age requirements\n3. Have a clean driving record\n4. Own or have access to a vehicle that meets platform requirements\n5. Pass the platform's background check\n6. Register as an individual driver with the ride-sharing platform\n\nIncorporation is not a requirement for driving for ride-sharing services in Manila. You can register as an individual driver directly through the app's registration process.",
